** ( NodeList ):

- Static collection of HTML elements by ( id, class, element )



** ( classList ):

- Element Property in Javascript used to interact 
  w/ an element's CSS class

 • add() //Adds a CSS class to an element 
 • remove() //Removes a CSS class to an element
 • toggle() //if present, Remove a CSS class to an element, if not add 
 • replace( oldClass, newClass ) //Replaces present class w/ a new class
 • contains //Returns true if Element uses that class 

( Example ):

 • Element_Holder.classList.add("Class");

 • Element_Holder.classList.remove("Class");

 • Element_Holder.classList.toggle("Class");

 • Element_Holder.classList.replace("OldClass", "NewClass");

 • if( Element_Holder.classList.contains("Class") ){ ... }
   else{ ... }



** ( Element Selectors ):

- methods used to target & manipulate HTML elements

- they allow you to select one or 
  multiple html elements from the DOM

  
( Example ):

 • const Element_Holder = document.getElementById("ID");
 // returns a single Element, that matches Inputted "ID" or NULL ( when not found )


 • const Element_Holder = document.getElementsClassName("Class"); 
 // returns an array of Elements, that matches Inputted "Class"
 

 • const Element_Holder = document.getElementsByTagName("Class"); 
 // returns an array of Elements, that matches Inputted "Tag" ( <h1>, <div>, <p> etc...)
   

 • const Element_Holder = document.querySelector("#ID" or ".Class" or "Tag"); 
 // returns a single Element, that 1st matches Inputted "ID", "Class", "Tag"
 // but strict w/ syntax ( Except for tag ), 
 // ID = #ID | Class = .Class | Tag = Tag

 
 • const Element_Holder = document.querySelectorAll("#ID" or ".Class" or "Tag"); 
 // same as the "document.querySelector" but, returns an array of Elements instead
 


** ( Mouse Events ):

- Event Listener, A function that waits for and responds to specific actions on a chosen element. 
  It allows your code to react when something happens.


( Syntax ):

 • Element_Holder.addEventListener( event, callback or function );


( List of Events ):

 • click, functions are activated, when an element with this event is clicked 
 • mouseover, functions are activated, when an element with this event is hovered
 • mouseout, the opposite of mouseover